        "score": 0.6276072,
        "text": "The document is a fee schedule from ERCOT effective October 1, 2024. It outlines various application and inspection fees related to energy generation and transmission services. Key points include:\n\n1. **Full Interconnection Study (FIS) Application Fee**: \n   - $3,000 for new generators.\n   - $2,700 for modifications to existing generators.\n\n2. **Qualified Scheduling Entity (QSE) and Related Fees**:\n   - $500 per entity for QSE, Sub-QSE, Competitive Retailer (CR), Congestion Revenue Right (CRR) Account Holder, Independent Market Information System Registered Entity (IMRE), Resource Entity, and Transmission/Distribution Service Providers (TDSPs).\n\n3. **Counter-Party Background Check Fee**:\n   - $350 per principal.\n\n4. **Weatherization Inspection Fees**:\n   - Resource Entities and Transmission Service Providers must pay fees for weatherization inspections as per Texas Administrative Code \u00a7 25.55.\n\nThe document specifies that fees are associated with modifications based on the cumulative megawatt (MW) amount of changes submitted within the last 12 months. If modifications are less than 10 MW, the fee is $2,300; if 10 MW or greater, the fee is $14,000.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Fee_Schedule/page_3.jpg",
          "page_num": 3,
          "title": "ERCOT Fee Schedule",
