      "highlights": [
        "ERCOT Releases New Documents to Streamline the Large Load Interconnection Process (Effective December 15, 2025) ... Published Dec 16, 2025\n + Follow \n### ERCOT Formalizes the Large Load Interconnection Process What Developers, Utilities, and TSPs Need to Know —Effective December 15, 2025 ERCOT has released new required documents to support theLarge Load Interconnection (LLI) processunderSection 9 of the ERCOT Planning Guide ( https://www.ercot.com/files/docs/2011/04/28/09-121525.docx ), marking a major milestone in how large demand projects are planned, studied, and energized across the ERCOT system. These two documents are posted here: Large Load Integration section of the ERCOT website EffectiveDecember 15, 2025, these changes implement key elements ofPGRR 115, aligned withNPRR 1234, establishing interconnection and modeling standards forloads 25 MW and greater. ... ERCOT’s latest action moves Large Load interconnection toward amore disciplined, front-loaded, and standardized ... ERCOT has posted two mandatory documents in theLarge Load Integrationsection of its website: 1. Load Information Form (LIF)A standardized intake form that consolidates all required Large Load project data, including: * MW size and ramp profile\n* Point(s) of Interconnection\n* Load characteristics and modeling inputs * Load Commissioning Plan (LCP)with phased energization details Link here: https://www.ercot.com/files/docs/2025/12/15/Load-Information-Form\\_v1.xlsx 2. Instructions for Submission of Project Data & CommunicationsA procedural guide defining: ... * LLIS initiation, updates, scopes, reports, and approvals\n## Recommended by LinkedIn ... nk> Use of these documents is nowmandatoryfor all Large Load interconnection submissions.\n### Who Is Impacted These requirements apply to:\n* Transmission & Distribution Service Providers (TDSPs)\n* Transmission Owners (TOs) * Interconnecting Large Load Entities (ILLEs)\n* Resource Entities (REs) and Interconnecting Entities (IEs) In short—any stakeholder involved in Large Load planning, studies, or energization in ERCOT. ... * [PJM Cycle 01"
